edas#SlideSet: The slideset is a child of the document which is the parent of the review.
edas#Review: The document review is the child of the document mealmenu.
edas#Programme: The child of a programme is a document which is parented by a paper.
edas#Paper: Paper is a child of a document, a slideset and a rejected paper. Acceptedpaper and ratedpaper are both parents of paper.
edas#MealMenu: The mealmenu is a child of the document which is the parent of the programme.
edas#Document: The document is the parent of the slideset, the mealmenu, and the pending paper.
edas#Topic: The topic of testonly is the parent of parallelanddistributedcomputing and communicationtheory. It is also the parent of computernetworks and computernetworksswitching.
edas#ConferenceEvent: The conferenceevent is the parent of the nonacademicevent and the academicevent. The socialevent is the parent of the excursion and the paperpresentation.
edas#Call: callforpapers and callforreviews are both parented by callformanuscripts.
edas#ReviewRating: Reviewrating is the parent of accpetifroomrating and week rejectrating. It is also the parent of acceptrating and rejectrating.
edas#Organization: The ngo and the government organizations are both parented by the ngo and the industry.
edas#Conference: The conference is equivalent to a singlelevelconference and is also equivalent to a twolevelconference. It is the child of Thing.
edas#PersonalHistory: personalhistory is the parent of personalreviewhistory and personalpublicationhistory.
edas#Sponsorship: The parent company of a sponsorship is travelgrant.
edas#ReviewQuestion: The review question is the parent of the numericalreview question and the textualreview question.
edas#Person: The parent of a tpcmember is the conferencechair, the attendee is the sessionchair and the reviewer is the sessionchair.
edas#Place: The meetingroom and the conference venue are both parented by the same place. The accommodation and dining places are also parented by the same place.
edas#WeekRejectRating: Reviewrating is the parent of rejectrating and is equivalent to reviewrating.
edas#AcceptRating: accpetifroomrating and acceptrating are both children of reviewrating.
edas#AccpetIfRoomRating: accpetifroomrating is equivalent to reviewrating and acceptrating.
edas#RejectRating: Reviewrating is the parent of weekrejectrating and is equivalent to reviewrating.
edas#MealEvent: The conferencedinner is a mealevent which is the parent of the conferencedinner. The breakevent is also the parent of the conferencedinner.
edas#NonAcademicEvent: The nonacademicevent is the parent of the conferenceevent and the academicevent. It is also the parent of the talkevent and the welcometalk. It is also the parent of the mealevent and the mealbreak.
edas#BreakEvent: breakevent is the parent of coffeebreak and mealbreak. It is also the child of conferenceevent and academicevent. It is also the parent of paper presentation.
edas#ParallelAndDistributedComputingTopi: Parallelanddistributedcomputing is a child of computernetworks which is parented by computernetworksenterprise.
edas#WirelessCommunicationsTopic: The wirelesscommunicationstopic is a child of the computernetworkstopic and the computernetworkssecuritytopic.
edas#OperatingTopicsystems: Operatingtopicsystems is a child of computernetworks which is parented to computernetworkssecurity.
edas#ComputerNetworksTopic: Computernetworks is the parent of computernetworksmanagement and computernetworksmeasurements. It is also the parent of computernetworkssensor and signal processing.
edas#SatelliteAndSpaceCommunicationsTopi: The satelliteandspacecommunicationstopic is a child of the operatingtopicsystems topic.
edas#CADTopic: The topic of cadtopic is the child of the topic of medicinetopic.
edas#MultimediaTopic: Microelectronicstopic is a child of multimediatopic.
edas#CommunicationsTopic: The topic of communications is the child of the topic of medicine.
edas#PowerlineTransmissionTopic: The powerlinetransmissiontopic is a child of the communicationtheorytopic.
edas#AntennasTopic: The antennastopic is a child of the performancetopic.
edas#PerformanceTopic: The performancetopic is a child of the computer architecturetopic.
edas#SignalProcessingTopic: The signal processing topic is a child of the multimedia topic.
edas#MicroelectronicsTopic: The microelectronicstopic is a child of the mobilecomputingtopic.
edas#TestOnlyTopic: testonlytopic is a child of testprocessingtopic.
edas#RadioCommunicationsTopic: Radiocommunicationstopic is a child of radiocommunicationstopic and is parented by cadtopic.
edas#ComputerArchitectureTopic: The computer architecture topic is a child of the cryptography topic.
edas#MedicineTopic: The topic of medicine is a child of the topic of computer architecture.
edas#SecurityTopic: The securitytopic is a child of the radiocommunicationstopic.
edas#MobileComputingTopic: The mobilecomputingtopic is a child of the communicationtheorytopic.
edas#CryptographyTopic: The cryptography topic is a child of the mobilecomputing topic.
edas#CommunicationTheoryTopic: The communicationtheorytopic is a child of the operatingtopicsystems topic.
edas#ConferenceChair: The conferencechair is the child of the parent of the tpcmember.
edas#Author: The author is the parent of the presenter and the conferencechair.
edas#DiningPlace: The dining place is the child of the conference venue.
edas#Presenter: The presenter is the child of the author who is the parent of the conferencechair.
edas#AcademiaOrganization: The academic organization is the child of the organization which is parented by the industry organization.
edas#IndustryOrganization: The industry organization is the child of the organization which is parented by the academic organization.
edas#NGO: ngo is a child of an organization which is parented by an industry organization.
edas#GovernmentOrganization: The government organization is the child of the organization which is parented by the industry organization.
edas#ComputerNetworksEnterpriseTopic: The computernetworksenterprisetopic is the child of the computernetworksenterprisetopic and the parent of the computernetworkssensortopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksSwitchingTopic: The computernetworksswitchingtopic is a child of the computernetworkstopic which is parented to the communicationstopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksSensorTopic: The computernetworkssensortopic is the child of the computernetworkssensortopic and the parent of computernetworksopticaltopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksSecurityTopic: The computernetworkssecuritytopic is a child of the computernetworkstopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksOpticalTopic: The computernetworksopticaltopic is a child of the computernetworkstopic and is parented to the computerarchitecturetopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksMeasurementsTopic: The computernetworkssensortopic is the child of the computernetworksmeasurementstopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksManagementTopic: The computernetworksmanagementtopic is a child of the computernetworkstopic.
edas#ComputerNetworksAapplicationsTopic: The computernetworksaapplicationstopic is the child of the computernetworksapplicationstopic and the parent of computernetworkssecuritytopic.
edas#ActivePaper: The activepaper is a child of paper and is the parent of pending papers and rated papers.
edas#PendingPaper: pendingpaper is a child of paper which is parented by withdrawnpaper.
edas#WithdrawnPaper: withdrawnpaper is a child of paper which is the parent of a programme.
edas#RejectedPaper: The rejected paper is a child of paper which is the parent of a programme.
edas#AcceptedPaper: Acceptedpaper is the child of paper and is the parent of withdrawnpaper.
edas#PublishedPaper: The published paper is the child of paper and is the parent of withdrawn paper.
edas#Attendee: The attendee is a child of the person who is the parent of tpcmember.
edas#CoffeeBreak: coffeebreak is equivalent to breakevent which is the parent of freetimebreak.
edas#FreeTimeBreak: breakevent is the parent of mealbreak and freetimebreak.
edas#MealBreak: Breakevents are similar to coffee breaks and a mealbreak is equivalent to a breakevent.
edas#Reviewer: The reviewer is the person who is the parent of tpcmember.
edas#ClosingTalk: closingtalk is a child of talkevent and welcometalk.
edas#WelcomeTalk: welcometalk is a child of talkevent and is the parent of closingtalk.
edas#TalkEvent: talkevent is the parent of organizationalmeeting, welcometalk and closingtalk.
edas#SessionChair: The sessionchair is a child of the person who is the parent of the conferencechair.
edas#TPCMember: tpcmember is a child of a person who is equivalent to a reviewer.
edas#TwoLevelConference: The twolevelconference is equivalent to the conference and the singlelevelconference.
edas#CallForPapers: callforpapers is the child of call and is the parent of callformanuscripts.
edas#TextualReviewQuestion: The textualreviewquestion is the child of the reviewquestion and the parent of the numericalreviewquestion.
edas#NumericalReviewQuestion: The numericalreviewquestion is the child of the reviewquestion and the parent of the textualreviewquestion.
edas#OrganizationalMeeting: The organizationalmeeting is the parent of the academicevent which is the parent of the paperpresentation.
edas#PaperPresentation: Paperpresentation is a child of academicevent and conferenceevent. Breakevent is a parent of conferenceevent and coffeebreak.
edas#Workshop: The workshop is the child of academicevent which is the parent of paperpresentation.
edas#AcademicEvent: The academicevent is the parent of the workshop and the organizationalmeeting. It is also the parent of the conferenceevent and the welcometalk.
edas#PersonalPublicationHistory: personalhistory is the child of personalpublicationhistory and is the parent of personalreviewhistory.
edas#Excursion: The excursion is a child of socialvent which is a child of conferenceevent and nonacademicevent.
edas#SocialEvent: The nonacademicevent is the parent of the mealevent, the conferencedinner, the reception and the excursion.
edas#CallForReviews: callforreviews is the child of call and is the parent of callforpapers.
edas#PersonalReviewHistory: personalreviewhistory is the child of personalhistory and is the parent of personalpublicationhistory.
edas#ConferenceVenuePlace: The conference venue is the child of the conference venue and the parent of the accommodation place.
edas#CallForManuscripts: callforreviews is the parent of callformanuscripts.
edas#Reception: The reception is child of the social event which is the parent of the academic event and the conferenceevent. The conferenceevent is also the parent of the workshop.
edas#SingleLevelConference: The singlelevelconference is equivalent to a conference which is a child of Thing.
edas#MeetingRoomPlace: The meetingroom is the child of the conference venue.
edas#AccommodationPlace: The accommodationplace is child of the meetingroomplace.
edas#RatedPapers: ratedpapers is the child of activepaper which is the parent of acceptedpaper.
edas#TravelGrant: The travel grant is a child of sponsorship.
edas#ConferenceDinner: The conferencedinner is a child of the mealevent which is a parent of the academicevent and the workshop. It is also a child of the nonacademicevent which is also a child of the conferencedinner.
